Document: PhysicsDirectSpaceState3DExtension
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsdirectspacestate3dextension.rst
Summary: Overview of the PhysicsDirectSpaceState3DExtension class used for creating custom physics space state implementations via GDExtension.

Inherits: PhysicsDirectSpaceState3D < RefCounted < Object

Description:
This class extends PhysicsDirectSpaceState3D by providing additional virtual methods that can be overridden. When these methods are overridden, they will be called instead of the internal methods of the physics server. This class is intended for use with GDExtension to create custom implementations of PhysicsDirectSpaceState3D.
---CHUNK---
Document: PhysicsDirectSpaceState3DExtension
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsdirectspacestate3dextension.rst
Summary: This section details the methods available in the PhysicsDirectSpaceState3DExtension class, focusing on physics queries and interactions within the 3D space.

Method: _cast_motion(shape_rid: RID, transform: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, margin: float, collision_mask: int, collide_with_bodies: bool, collide_with_areas: bool, closest_safe: float*, closest_unsafe: float*, info: PhysicsServer3DExtensionShapeRestInfo*) → bool
This method is part of the virtual interface for extending the physics engine. It is required and used to determine the motion of a shape within the physics space, considering collisions.

Method: _collide_shape(shape_rid: RID, transform: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, margin: float, collision_mask: int, collide_with_bodies: bool, collide_with_areas: bool, results: void*, max_results: int, result_count: int32_t*) → bool
This method is part of the virtual interface for extending the physics engine. It is required and used to find collisions for a given shape's motion within the physics space.

Method: _get_closest_point_to_object_volume(object: RID, point: Vector3) → Vector3
This method is part of the virtual interface for extending the physics engine. It is required and used to find the closest point on an object's volume to a given point in space. It is a const method.

Method: _intersect_point(position: Vector3, collision_mask: int, collide_with_bodies: bool, collide_with_areas: bool, results: PhysicsServer3DExtensionShapeResult*, max_results: int) → int
This method is part of the virtual interface for extending the physics engine. It is required and used to find shapes that intersect a specific point in space, considering collision masks and types.

Method: _intersect_ray(from: Vector3, to: Vector3, collision_mask: int, collide_with_bodies: bool, collide_with_areas: bool, hit_from_inside: bool, hit_back_faces: bool, pick_ray: bool, result: PhysicsServer3DExtensionRayResult*) → bool
This method is part of the virtual interface for extending the physics engine. It is required and used to perform a raycast in the physics space to detect intersections with shapes.

Method: _intersect_shape(shape_rid: RID, transform: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, margin: float, collision_mask: int, collide_with_bodies: bool, collide_with_areas: bool, result_count: PhysicsServer3DExtensionShapeResult*, max_results: int) → int
This method is part of the virtual interface for extending the physics engine. It is required and used to find shapes that intersect with another shape's motion within the physics space.

Method: _rest_info(shape_rid: RID, transform: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, margin: float, collision_mask: int, collide_with_bodies: bool, collide_with_areas: bool, rest_info: PhysicsServer3DExtensionShapeRestInfo*) → bool
This method is part of the virtual interface for extending the physics engine. It is required and used to get information about the rest state of a shape when it comes to rest within the physics space.

Method: is_body_excluded_from_query(body: RID) → bool
This method is a const method that checks if a specific physics body is excluded from queries within the physics space.